        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">The Staff IS that good, if you take the time to learn how to integrate it into your play style.</P><P>Your life changes when you get a staff of the dreaded gaze.  No longer must you worry about pets dying.  I used to walk into skyfire with 6 bone chips at 54 because I knew it would be plenty for all day.  The fear staff saves you SO much mana it's not even funny, it's worth every second you camp it.  And yes, it probably still drops, it's just that rare.</P><P>I used to pull my mob, run back to camp, hit it with darkness and then run ahead to max spell distance and hit the staff.  It would go off about 2 seconds before the mob got to me, once feared, stack on Cessation, Ebolt or whatever you're using, and hit the staff again.  Then sit down for 25 seconds, stand up, hit the staff, redark and sit again.</P><P>If fear from the staff EVER gets resisted, your invoke fear spell is ready to go the INSTANT you see the resist message, and the mob is feared 2.5 seconds later....not the 10 seconds you'd normally have to wait.</P><P>I can't figure out why people say the cast time is too long and it's not worth the camp.  They must be trying to replace their invoke fear spell slot with the staff.  It doesn't work like that.  It doesn't let you un-mem fear completely and depend on the staff.  It's a tool that complements your spell line up, and it complements it very nicely.</P><P>It still sits in my tink bag even though i've been 60 for months, a damned useful tool and I can't see myself ever selling it.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
